quran[14]{c,v,t}:
  109,1,"Say, \"O You who deny the Truth, and, thus, by remaining ungrateful to the Creator's Ultimate Guidance, choose to live in darkness"
  109,2,"I do not worship that which you worship. (Neither your idols, nor your tenets, nor your moral values, way of life, nor your holy men or leaders)"
  109,3,Nor do you worship that which I worship
  109,4,And I will never worship that which you have ever worshiped
  109,5,Nor (unless you see the Light) will you worship that which I worship
  109,6,"Unto you your way, and unto me my Way"
  110,1,When comes Allah's Help and the Victory
  110,2,And you see the people enter Allah's Religion in throngs
  110,3,"(Think not that your job is done). Then strive hard to make the Divine System a living witness to the Glory and Praise of your Lord. And you shall remain vigilant to guard the System as a helmet guards the head. Behold, He is ever Responsive to your efforts"
  111,1,"Perished is the power of Abi Lahab, and perished is he"
  111,2,"His wealth and gains will avail him not! (69:27-28), ("
  111,3,"He shall have to endure a fire blazing, glowing"
  111,4,"And his wife, that carrier of slanderous tales, the firewood hauler"
  111,5,"Will have her neck ornamented with a rope of palm-fiber. ((17:13). 'Jeed' = A neck decorated with an ornament"